OL,3,CFamily say crash victim was 'a big kid
OL,4,Cwith a heart of gold'
OL,6,FThe family of a motorcyclist who died
OL,7,Ffollowing a two-vehicle crash have
OL,8,Fdescribed him as a "big kid, with an
OL,9,Fadventurous spirit and a heart of
OL,10,Fgold."
OL,12,FDavid Eardley, from Melksham, was
OL,13,Friding his motorbike along the A342
OL,14,FMonument Hill, near Devizes, when he
OL,15,Fwas involved in a collision with a
OL,16,FCitroen van shortly after 10am on
OL,17,FSaturday 27 July.
OL,19,FThe 67 year-old died at the scene,
OL,20,FWiltshire Police said.
